ecologylab.semantics.actions
Class SemanticActionHandler<C extends Container,IC extends InfoCollector<C>>

java.lang.Object
  ecologylab.generic.Debug
      ecologylab.semantics.actions.SemanticActionHandler<C,IC>
All Implemented Interfaces:
SemanticActionNamedArguments, SemanticActionsKeyWords, SemanticActionStandardMethods
public abstract class SemanticActionHandler<C extends Container,IC extends InfoCollector<C>>
extends ecologylab.generic.Debug
implements SemanticActionStandardMethods, SemanticActionsKeyWords, SemanticActionNamedArguments

This is the handler for semantic actions. It contains a list of abstract method for the semantic action possible. It has a handleSemanticAction method which decides what action to take when a semantic action is passed to it. If a new semantic action has to be added we must add a case to handle that in this method. There is one SemanticActionHandler created for each DocumentType.connect TODO Might want to implement lexical scoping in variables.

Author:
amathur
